import React from 'react';
import LogEntry from './LogEntry.js';
   
class Logger extends React.Component {

    templateData = {
        Day: {},
        Location: {},
        Swell: {},
        Wind: {},
        Tide: {},
        Conditions: {},
        Comments: {}
    };

    constructor(props) {
        super(props);
        this.log = this.templateData;
        this.state = {
            date: new Date(),
            log: {}
        };
        this.updateLog = this.updateLog.bind(this);
        this.getStateLog = this.getStateLog.bind(this);
    }

    updateLog(groupTitle, label, selected, set) {
        this.log[groupTitle][label] = selected;
        if (groupTitle !== undefined && groupTitle !== 1 && selected !== undefined && set) {
            this.setState({log: this.log});
        }
    }
    getStateLog = () => this.state.log;

    writeLog = () => {
        let savedLogs = localStorage.getItem("surfLog") || "";
        savedLogs = `${savedLogs},
${JSON.stringify(this.state.log, null, 2)}`;
        console.log(`LocalStorage: ${JSON.stringify(savedLogs,null, 2)}`)
        localStorage.setItem("surfLog", JSON.stringify(savedLogs,null, 2));
        /*
        let data;
        const returnJSON = (response) => response.json();
        const returnRejection = (response) => Promise.reject({status: response.status, data});
        const validate = (response) => (response.ok) ? returnJSON(response) : returnRejection(response);
        const uri = 'http://localhost:8080/writeSurfLog.json';
        fetch(uri)
            .then(response => validate(response))
            .then(data => JSON.stringify(data))
            .then(log => console.log(log))
            .catch(err => console.log("Something went wrong!\n", err));
        */
    }

        console.log(`Logger => ${JSON.stringify(this.state, null, 2)}`)
        //FunctionalWrite("/surfLog.json", this.state.log);
